        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You can't cast spells but mimic spellwork well enough to convince others you have magical powers. You've pretended to be a magical adept for so long you've learned to fool magic items into working at your touch.</p>\n<p>Choose two attribute boosts. One must be to <strong>Wisdom</strong> or <strong>Charisma</strong>, and one is a free attribute boost.</p>\n<p>You're trained in the Deception skill and a magic tradition skill of your choice (Arcana, Nature, Occultism, or Religion). You gain the @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.feats.Item.Trick Magic Item] skill feat.</p>"
